<subSubSection pageId="89" pageNumber="847" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="89.[718,1315,2292,2715]" pageId="89" pageNumber="847">
Systematic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[1042,1183,2366,2399]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="847" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platyops">E. platyops</taxonomicName>
is uncertain. It is often considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[719,895,2449,2478]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="847" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hottentotus">E. hottentotus</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[943,1092,2449,2478]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="847" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
, but it is generally considered a distinct species based on morphology. Revision of African 
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1314,2524,2557]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="847" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eptesicus</taxonomicName>
is needed. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
